bug.short_desc: Sorting in the table can be wrong

long_desc.thetext: The current showcase shows a table filled with data from YQL. The year field is filled with strings containing "2008", "2009" and "". Sorting this column works fine as long no other column has been sorted before. Changing the sort order of many columns and sorting again the year can cause a wrong sort order (i haven't found a way to reproduce it reliable).
Created attachment 682 See the wrong sorted year column.
Fixed with r21259. The table was not capable of NaN in number columns.
